DIGEST
SB 296 Original 2026 Regular Session Kleinpeter
Present law provides that the Louisiana Wildlife and Fisheries Commission consist of seven
members to be appointed by the governor.
Proposed law increases the membership from 7 to 9.
Proposed law becomes effective if, as, and when the amendment to the constitution proposed
by SB _ of the 2026 R.S. is adopted at a statewide election and becomes effective.
(Amends R.S. 36:601(A) and R.S. 56:1(B) and (C))
